The paper focuses on using EEG signals for content-based image retrieval, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of Brain Computer Interfaces (BCI) also involves neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with image retrieval and presentation. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with retrieving relevant objects from a dataset.
